modules.description: This module controls whether stdout is treated as a terminal, overriding the default behavior for testing purposes. It provides a mutable reference `force_stdout_isatty_test` that, when set to true, forces the pager logic to behave as if stdout is a TTY. This allows tests to simulate interactive output scenarios even when stdout is not a terminal.

This module runs a Git-configured pager to display long outputs like diffs, handling color settings and output destinations based on Git's configuration. It provides functions to write content to the pager, control color output, and determine the type of output being used. It is ideal for Git-integrated tools that need to display colored, paginated output to users while respecting their Git settings.
